@Lethain Yes, would strongly recommend it for Director+ roles. 

Many of our interviewers have experience with this style. We conduct a paired interview where one person engages in conversation and the other takes detailed notes - serves as organic training.

I am personally thrilled to have the opportunity to work closely with @mmbronstein, @frederickmonti, and the @fabula_ai team. Welcome to the flock, Fabula!
The Fabula team‚Äôs expertise in geometric deep learning is applicable to many problems at Twitter. The team will initially focus on improving the health of the public conversation.
We have a strategic interest in improving graph deep learning methods at Twitter as we build out a research group to advance the state of the art in machine learning.

Geometric deep learning aims to bring key ingredients of deep learning methods such as convolutional neural networks to non-Euclidean data, and the Fabula team has pioneered important work in this area.

Deep learning has been very successful in modeling images, video, and speech, all of which contain an underlying Euclidean structure. However, a wide range of problems at Twitter benefit immensely from the ability to model and learn from non-Euclidean graph structured data.
